President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 10, 2013, as Military Spouse Appreciation Day. In the proclamation, he acknowledges the important role that military spouses play in supporting their partners who serve in the military. He emphasizes the need to provide support and assistance to military spouses, including childcare, education, and employment opportunities. The President also highlights the efforts of the Joining Forces initiative, led by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden, to partner with the private sector in expanding hiring for military spouses and veterans. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to honor military spouses through appropriate ceremonies and activities.